# Helm packs the whole chart directory into the release secret, which is capped at
# 1 MB. Nothing below is used to RENDER the chart — src, static and data are baked
# into the container image at build time, and tools only ever runs on a laptop.
# Leave them in and `helm upgrade` fails with "Secret ... is invalid: data: Too long".
.git/
# The dev venv (see memory: local dev) — a >5MB python binary via symlink.
.venv/
src/
static/
tools/
data/
# ~220 MB of read-only lineage (GamePicker alone carries a 189 MB exclusives/
# dump). Nothing here is deployed; leaving it in blows the 1 MB cap instantly.
reference/
Dockerfile
build.sh
upgrade.sh
README.md
TODO.md
*.tar
*.png
*.jpg
*.mjs
.gitignore
values.local.yaml
